			"<div id = \"section_2\"><span id = \"Syntax\"></span><h3 class = \"editable\">Syntax</h3>\n<p><code><em>obj</em>.__lookupSetter__(<em>sprop</em>)</code></p>\n</div>",
			"<div id = \"section_3\"><span id = \"Parameters\"></span><h3 class = \"editable\">Parameters</h3>\n<dl> <dt><code>sprop</code></dt> <dd>a string containing the name of the property whose setter should be returned</dd>\n</dl>\n</div>",
			"<div id = \"section_4\"><span id = \"Description\"></span><h3 class = \"editable\">Description</h3>\n<p>If a setter has been defined for an object's property, it's not possible to reference the setter function through that property, because that property refers to the return value of that function. <code>__lookupSetter__</code> can be used to obtain a reference to the setter function.</p>\n</div>",
